            <br /><br /><br />
            <p><h2>Books</h2></p>
		<ul>I found <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Chemical-Sensitivity-Sherry-Rogers/dp/0879836342/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1454868956&sr=8-1&keywords=ISBN-13%3A+978-0879836344" target="_blank">this</a> book to be a wealth of information. It does contain quite a bit of medical jargon and may be a bit outdated on some information.</ul>
		<ul>There is a doctor in Toronto that has reseached and <a href="http://johnmolot.com/books/" target="_blank">written books</a> on environmental illness and it's causes.</ul>
		<ul>A book review of <a href="http://vitalitymagazine.com/book-reviews/review/prostituting-science-the-psychologisation-of-mcs-cfs-and-ehs-for-political-/" target="_blank">Prostituting Science</a> The Psychologisation of MCS, CFS and EHS for Political Gain</ul>
<br /><br /><br />
	<p><h2>Fragrance Information</h2></p>
	<img src="images/fragrances.jpg" alt="But I'm not wearing fragrance.">
		<p><a href="http://www.womensvoices.org/2015/12/10/toxic-chemicals-found-in-fragrance/" target="_blank">What</a> is in your fragrances?</p>
		<p>The fragrance industry has <a href="http://www.ifraorg.org/en-us/ingredients" target="_blank">published</a> a list of chemicals commonly used in fragrances. Are you ok with wearing these?</p>
		<p>A fragrance <a href="http://www.healthyenvironmentforkids.ca/sites/healthyenvironmentforkids.ca/files/CPCHE_FactsFragrancesEN.pdf" target="_blank">fact sheet.</a></p>		
		<p>A BBC article on <a href="http://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-35281338" target="_blank">fragrances</a></p>   
		<p>Here is a Youtube <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GsZizyL_Llc&feature=youtu.be" target="_blank">PSA</a> about fragrances and the problems they cause.</p>
		<p>Can fragrances cause <a href="http://www.nydailynews.com/life-style/health/scented-candles-cleaning-products-release-cancerous-agents-article-1.2500627" target="_blank">cancer?</a></p>
		<p>Here is another article from <a href="http://www.msn.com/en-us/health/medical/new-study-finds-scented-candles-and-air-fresheners-pose-dangerous-health-risks/ar-AAdX6dD" target="_blank">MSN.</a></p>
		<p>Are fragrance manufacturers watching out for <a href="http://www.fairwarning.org/2016/01/doubts-raised-about-chemical-stew-in-fragrances-used-in-consumer-products/" target="_blank">the consumer?</a></p>
		<p>An interesting post on how an industry can violate people's <a href="https://lindasepp.wordpress.com/2015/03/09/what-if-an-industry-was-allowed-to-disable-us-and-keep-us-housebound/" target="_blank">rights.</a></p>
		<p>What are your <a href="https://sondasmcschatter.wordpress.com/2013/02/20/mcs-signs-mcs-protocol/" target="_blank">fragrances</a> doing to yourself and others. They have more of an impact than you think.</p>
		<p>An article from <a href="http://www.motherjones.com/environment/2016/01/toxic-chemicals-fragrance-cosmetics-safety" target="_blank">Mother Jones</a> about the safety of fragrances.</p>
<br /><br /><br />
		<h2>Work Resources</h2>
		<p><a href="https://askjan.org/media/MCS.html" target="_blank">Information from the Job Accomodation Network</a></p>
   <p>An interesting <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aJuBuXXMaiA" target="_blank">documentary</a> about Chemical Sensitivity in the workplace.</p>
   <p>Is your workplace being <a href="http://johnmolot.com/2015/02/23/why-do-employees-with-mcs-struggle-for-accommodation-and-benefits/" target="_blank">discriminatory</a> against the Chemically injured?</p>
   <p><a href="https://lindasepp.wordpress.com/2013/09/27/how-to-enforce-a-fragrance-free-policy/" target="_blank">How to enforce a workplace fragrance free policy</a></p>
   <p>MCS may be <a href="http://employment.findlaw.com/employment-discrimination/chemical-sensitivities-discrimination.html" target="_blank">covered</a> under the ADA</p>
   <p>It's odd to think of myself as being <a href="http://www.hud.gov/offices/adm/hudclips/lops/GME-0009LOPS.pdf" target="_blank">handicapped</a> but it is something that is always there.</p>
   <p>A <a href="http://www.aabri.com/manuscripts/09244.pdf" target="_blank">PDF</a> on what managers should know about Chemical Sensitivity.</p><br/><br/><br/>
	<p><h2>Alternatives for skin and body care</h2></p>
		<ul>Did you know that <a href="http://honeyfanatic.com/163/homemade-honey-mask-recipe-a-secret-to-younger-looking-skin/" target="_blank">honey</a> can be good for your skin?</ul>
		<ul>Herbal <a href="http://www.realnatural.org/herbal-cough-remedy-beats-pharma-cough-syrup/" target="_blank">cough remedy</a> performs better than OTC versions</ul>	
		<ul><a href="http://draxe.com/beeswax/" target="_blank">Beeswax</a> has some interesting health benefits.</ul>	
<br /><br /><br />
	<p><h2>Clean air</h2></p>
		<ul>An organization fighting for clean indoor air can be found <a href="http://cleanerindoorair.org/" target="_blank">here</a></ul>
		<ul>Plants can make your home <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/58KFJzpJb2kyLtDPhhHqnbQ/are-perfumed-products-bad-for-me" target="_blank">healthier.</a></ul>
		<ul>A list of 6 <a href="http://www.healthdigezt.com/6-natural-air-purifiers/" target="_blank">air purifying plants.</a></ul>
		<ul>Here is a list of <a href="http://www.mnn.com/health/healthy-spaces/photos/15-houseplants-for-improving-indoor-air-quality/a-breath-of-fresh-air#top-desktop" target="_blank">15 air purifying plants.</a></ul>
		<ul>Here are some options if you have more of a <a href="http://simpleorganiclife.org/9-houseplants/" target="_blank">black thumb</a> instead of green.</ul>
<br /><br /><br />
	<p><h2>Information about chemicals in our environment</h2></p>
		<ul>There is a new <a href="http://madesafe.org/" target="_blank">certification website</a> for manufacturers producing healthy products.</ul>		
		<ul>The <a href="http://householdproducts.nlm.nih.gov/index.htm" target="_blank">National Institute of Health</a> has a website listing what is in common products and their health effects.</ul>
		<ul><a href="http://www.environmentalhealthnews.org/ehs/news/glycol-ethers-and-allergies" target="_blank">Water based paints</a> may be hazardous to your kids.</ul>
		<ul>There are Petrochemicals in <a href="https://lindasepp.wordpress.com/2014/03/23/theres-petrochemicals-in-what/" target="_blank">what?</a></ul>
		<ul>What can <a href="https://oecotextiles.wordpress.com/2016/02/19/whats-wrong-with-red-lists/" target="_blank">textiles</a> contain?</ul>
		<ul>How to determine <a href="http://it-takes-time.com/2016/02/toxic-mold-and-possessions-2.html" target="_blank">a course of action for mold.</a></ul>
		<ul>What about the hidden <a href="http://ecowatch.com/2016/02/21/products-that-contain-lead/" target="_blank">lead</a> in our lives?</ul>
<br /><br /><br />
	<p><h2>MCS coping resources</h2></p>
		<ul><a href="http://safecanarynest.org/" target="_blank">Resources for a MCS newbie</a></ul>
		<ul><a href="http://www.mcsrr.org/resources/articles/S3.html" target="_blank">This site</a> has some protocols for surviving Chemical Injury</ul>
		<ul>A MCS <a href="http://mcs-america.org/mcsfactsheet.pdf" target="_blank">Fact sheet</a></ul>
		<ul>The <a href="http://themighty.com/2015/11/to-the-doctors-of-chronic-illness-patients/" target="_blank">patient side</a> of the doctor/patient relationship with chronic illness.</ul>
		<ul>World Library of <a href="http://toxipedia.org/dosearchsite.action?queryString=mcs" target="_blank">Toxicology</a> articles on MCS.</ul>
		<ul>A very good <a href="https://tiltedmom.com/2016/02/19/planning-for-my-reactions/" target="_blank">blog post</a> about being prepared for a reaction to something.</ul>
		<ul>A good post on <a href="http://it-takes-time.com/2016/02/safe-bed-and-bedding.html" target="_blank">nontoxic bedding.</a></ul>
		<ul>There is a Chemical Sensitivity <a href="http://www.chemicalsensitivityfoundation.org/index.html" target="_blank">foundation.</a></ul>
		<ul>Chronic Neuroimmune Diseases <a href="http://www.anapsid.org/cnd/mcs/index.html" target="_blank">resources</a></ul>	
<br /><br /><br />	
	<p><h2>Other Medical information</h2></p>
		<ul>Here is an interesting article on how to reduce <a href="http://www.the-open-mind.com/simple-and-effective-spine-line-foot-massage-to-reverse-back-pain-fast/" target="_blank">lower back pain.</a></ul>
		<ul>Did you know that <a href="http://www.sciencealert.com/scientists-discover-that-sighing-is-actually-a-life-saving-biological-function" target="_blank">sighing</a> is healthy?</ul>	
		<ul>Are you aware of what it means to really <a href="http://johnmolot.com/2016/01/07/diet-and-detox/" target="_blank">detox?</a></ul>
		<ul>Is it just diet and exercise issues that cause <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3279464/" target="_blank">Obesity?</a></ul>
		<ul><a href="http://www.healthychild.org/what-caused-your-childs-allergic-skin-reaction/" target="_blank">What</a> caused your child's allergic skin reaction?</ul>
		<ul>MCS often progresses into <a href="http://themighty.com/2016/02/18-pe0ple-describe-what-chronic-fatigue-feels-like/" target="_blank">Chronic Fatigue Syndrome</a> and the symptoms are often the same.</ul>
		<ul>Pet treatments can be <a href="http://www.healthychild.org/common-pet-treatments-can-harm-young-children/" target="_blank">harmful</a> to children</ul>
		<ul>Are <a href="https://drjulissa.wordpress.com/2013/01/27/are-you-a-host-to-parasites/" target="_blank">parasites</a> a problem?</ul>
		<ul>Is your gut <a href="http://draxe.com/4-steps-to-heal-leaky-gut-and-autoimmune-disease/" target="_blank">leaky?</a></ul>
		<ul>Here is a <a href="http://the-labyrinth.com/2016/02/16/is-stewed-apple-the-perfect-functional-food-for-a-dysfunctional-gut/" target="_blank">post</a> about a possible cure for leaky gut.</ul>
		<ul>Eating fruits is really <a href="http://www.realnatural.org/fruits-reduce-inflammation-and-heart-disease/" target="_blank">heart healthy</a> in spite of claims to the contrary.</ul>
		<ul>What's in that <a href="http://grist.org/living/is-my-tattoo-full-of-toxic-chemicals/" target="_blank">tattoo?</a></ul>
		<ul>It may be possible to reverse dental <a href="http://draxe.com/naturally-reverse-cavities-heal-tooth-decay/">cavities</a> naturally.</ul>
		<ul>Is <a href="http://www.healthnutnews.com/draft-fluoride-officially-classified-as-a-neurotoxin-in-worlds-most-prestigious-medical-journal/" target="_blank">flouride</a> poisoning you?</ul>
	<br /><br /><br />	
	<p><h2>Can what you eat and drink hurt you?</h2></p>
		<ul>A story about <a href="https://rhondagessner.wordpress.com/2013/09/02/a-killer-in-your-fridge-sweet-poison-a-must-read/" target="_blank">sugar replacements.</a></ul>	
		<ul>BPA free may not be as <a href="https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2016/02/160201103543.htm" target="_blank">healthy</a> as we thought</ul>
	<br /><br /><br />	
	<p><h2>Healthy alternatives</h2></p>
		<p><h3>	Toys</h3></p>	
			<ul>Greener <a href="http://www.inhabitots.com/eco-bricks-are-made-from-cherry-wood-for-greener-lego-play/" target="_blank">LEGO</a> alternative</ul>
		<br /><br /><br />
		<p><h3>Cleaning</h3></p>	
			<ul>Did you know you can clean hardwood with <a href="http://it-takes-time.com/2016/02/black-tea-wood-floor-cleaner.html" target="_blank">tea?</a></ul>
			<ul>Norwex has a broad line of nontoxic cleaning products. I get mine <a href="http://www.norwex.biz/pws/luciareynolds/tabs/home.aspx" target="_blank">here.</a></ul>
			<ul>You can also clean with <a href="http://www.earth911.com/living-well-being/health/cleaning-vinegar-baking-soda-lemon/" target="_blank">baking soda, vinegar, and lemon.</a></ul>
		<br /><br /><br />		
		<p><h3>Food</h3></p>	
			<ul>Did you know you should be sprouting <a href="http://life.ca/2016/02/28/soaking-and-sprouting-seeds-nuts-and-grains/" target="_blank">nuts and grains?</a></ul>
			<ul>Anyone brave enough to try <a href="https://grownandgathered.wordpress.com/2016/03/02/apple-cider-vinegar-fire-tonic-2/" target="_blank">this?</a></ul>	
			<ul>Is a refrigerator always the <a href="http://life.ca/2016/02/29/back-to-basics-food-storage/" target="_blank">best</a> way to store your food?</ul>	
                 
